---
name: Changelog Generation
description: >-
  Generates or updates CHANGELOG.md from merged pull requests. On schedule or workflow_dispatch,
  rewrites the Unreleased section. On prep-release-* pull requests, rewrites the concrete release
  section. Uses a deterministic pre-activation phase to resolve the previous release tag, compare
  range, merged PR set, and target section mode, then an agent phase to generate changelog content
  strictly from PR-level summaries with full provenance.
on:
  schedule:
    - cron: daily
  workflow_dispatch:
  pull_request_target:
    branches:
      - main
    types: [opened, synchronize, reopened]
  steps:
    - name: Checkout repository
      uses: actions/checkout@v4
      with:
        fetch-depth: 0
        fetch-tags: true
    - name: Resolve release context
      id: resolve_release_context
      uses: actions/github-script@v8
      with:
        github-token: ${{ secrets.GITHUB_TOKEN }}
        x-script-include: scripts/resolve-release-context.inline.js
    - name: Gather PR evidence
      id: gather_pr_evidence
      uses: actions/github-script@v8
      env:
        PREVIOUS_TAG: ${{ steps.resolve_release_context.outputs.previous_tag }}
        COMPARE_RANGE: ${{ steps.resolve_release_context.outputs.compare_range }}
        MODE: ${{ steps.resolve_release_context.outputs.mode }}
        TARGET_VERSION: ${{ steps.resolve_release_context.outputs.target_version }}
      with:
        github-token: ${{ secrets.GITHUB_TOKEN }}
        x-script-include: scripts/gather-pr-evidence.inline.js
    - name: Upload release evidence artifact
      if: steps.gather_pr_evidence.outputs.has_evidence == 'true'
      uses: actions/upload-artifact@v4
      with:
        name: changelog-release-evidence
        path: ${{ steps.gather_pr_evidence.outputs.evidence_file_path }}
        if-no-files-found: error
if: >-
  (github.event_name != 'pull_request_target' ||
  startsWith(github.head_ref, 'prep-release-')) &&
  needs.pre_activation.outputs.has_evidence == 'true'
steps:
  - name: Download release evidence artifact
    uses: actions/download-artifact@v4
    with:
      name: changelog-release-evidence
      path: /tmp/gh-aw/agent
  - name: Verify evidence manifest path
    run: test -f /tmp/gh-aw/agent/evidence.json
  - name: Setup Go
    uses: actions/setup-go@v6
    with:
      go-version-file: go.mod
      cache: false
  - name: Export Go paths for AWF chroot mode
    run: |
      echo "GOROOT=$(go env GOROOT)" >> "$GITHUB_ENV"
      echo "GOPATH=$(go env GOPATH)" >> "$GITHUB_ENV"
      echo "GOMODCACHE=$(go env GOMODCACHE)" >> "$GITHUB_ENV"
  - name: Setup Node.js
    uses: actions/setup-node@v6
    with:
      node-version-file: package.json
  - name: Setup repository dependencies
    run: make setup
engine:
  id: claude
  model: "llm-gateway/gpt-5.5"
  version: 2.1.98
  env:
    ANTHROPIC_BASE_URL: "https://elastic.litellm-prod.ai"
    ANTHROPIC_API_KEY: ${{ secrets.CLAUDE_LITELLM_PROXY_API_KEY }}
permissions:
  contents: read
  pull-requests: read
jobs:
  pre-activation:
    outputs:
      mode: ${{ steps.resolve_release_context.outputs.mode }}
      previous_tag: ${{ steps.resolve_release_context.outputs.previous_tag }}
      compare_range: ${{ steps.resolve_release_context.outputs.compare_range }}
      target_version: ${{ steps.resolve_release_context.outputs.target_version }}
      target_branch: ${{ steps.resolve_release_context.outputs.target_branch }}
      has_evidence: ${{ steps.gather_pr_evidence.outputs.has_evidence }}
tools:
  github:
    toolsets: [repos, pull_requests]
network:
  allowed: [defaults, node, go, elastic.litellm-prod.ai]
checkout:
  fetch-depth: 0
safe-outputs:
  push-to-pull-request-branch:
    target: triggering
    max: 1
  create-pull-request:
    max: 1
    preserve-branch-name: true
  update-pull-request:
    max: 1
  noop:
    max: 1
    report-as-issue: false
---

# Changelog Generation

You generate or update `CHANGELOG.md` strictly from the merged pull-request evidence in workflow memory. You do **not** narrate individual commits, invent entries without PR backing, or guess user impact. Every changelog bullet MUST come from a PR in the evidence manifest. Never reference a PR number or URL that does not appear in the manifest.

## Pre-activation context

Deterministic pre-activation steps have already resolved the release context and gathered PR evidence. Do **not** re-query git or GitHub for commit lists or PR metadata; use the values below and the evidence manifest in workflow memory.

- **Mode**: `${{ needs.pre_activation.outputs.mode }}` — either `unreleased` (schedule/dispatch) or `release` (prep-release-* PR)
- **Previous tag**: `${{ needs.pre_activation.outputs.previous_tag }}`
- **Compare range**: `${{ needs.pre_activation.outputs.compare_range }}`
- **Target version** (release mode only): `${{ needs.pre_activation.outputs.target_version }}`
- **Target branch**: `${{ needs.pre_activation.outputs.target_branch }}`

## Evidence manifest

Read the evidence manifest from workflow memory at:
```
/tmp/gh-aw/agent/evidence.json
```

The manifest contains:
- `mode`, `target_version`, `previous_tag`, `compare_range`, `target_section`, `target_section_mode`
- `pull_requests[]`: each entry has `number`, `title`, `url`, `merge_commit_sha`, `author`, `labels`, `touched_files`, `classification` (`user-facing` | `internal` | `uncertain`), `inclusion_rationale`, `exclusion_rationale`

## Execution steps

1. **Read the evidence manifest** from workflow memory (path above).

2. **Read `CHANGELOG.md`** to understand the current structure, sub-heading style, and target section.

3. **Determine which PRs to include**:
   - PRs classified as `user-facing` SHOULD always be included unless you have a clear specific reason not to.
   - PRs classified as `uncertain`: use your judgment based on PR title, description, and `touched_files`. Include if they touch provider implementation paths (`internal/`, `pkg/`, `libs/`, `provider/`, `go.mod`) and have a meaningful, user-visible title. Exclude automated-sounding entries (e.g., dependency bumps, CI changes, doc-only).
   - PRs classified as `internal` MAY be omitted. Include only if you have a specific reason the user impact is significant.
   - Never include a PR entry without its `number` and `url` from the manifest.
   - Never invent PR numbers. Every bullet MUST end with `([#NNN](url))` or `([#NNN](url), [#MMM](url))` citation format using real PR numbers from the manifest.

4. **Pre-write validation rules** (enforce before generating):
   - Every changelog bullet MUST be backed by exactly one or more PRs from the evidence manifest.
   - No commit-level narration (e.g., bullets referencing commit SHAs or "Fix typo in xyz.go" without PR backing).
   - No fabricated PR numbers not present in the evidence.
   - If there are no user-facing PRs in the evidence, emit `noop` with a clear reason.

5. **Generate the changelog section**:

   For **`unreleased`** mode:
   - Rewrite **only** the `## [Unreleased]` section of `CHANGELOG.md`.
   - Preserve all other sections (previous release sections) exactly as-is.
   - Match the existing sub-heading style used in the file (look at current sections — the file uses e.g. `### Changes`, `### Breaking changes`). Do **not** invent sub-headings not already used in the file.
   - Each bullet: `- <summary> ([#<number>](<url>))`

   For **`release`** mode:
   - Emit the concrete `## [${{ needs.pre_activation.outputs.target_version }}] - <today's date in YYYY-MM-DD format>` section for this release run.
   - Remove any existing `## [Unreleased]` section (header and body). If the target version section already exists, replace that block; otherwise write the release section where Unreleased was (same dual-range splice as `rewriteChangelogSection` / `changelog-rewriter.js`).
   - Preserve every other release section unchanged. Preserve the trailing link-definition footer verbatim, including `[Unreleased]: ...`; remove only the `## [Unreleased]` *section block* (the heading plus its body up to the next `## [` heading), not those footer link-definition lines themselves.

6. **Write provenance JSON** to `/tmp/gh-aw/agent/provenance.json`. This file is written to workflow memory only — it is ephemeral support data and MUST NOT be added to the git index or committed. The file must contain machine-readable provenance mapping each bullet to its backing PR:

   ```json
   {
     "generated_at": "<ISO timestamp>",
     "mode": "<unreleased|release>",
     "target_version": "<version or empty>",
     "compare_range": "<range>",
     "bullets": [
       {
         "text": "Add resource X (#123)",
         "pr_numbers": [123],
         "pr_urls": ["https://github.com/.../pull/123"]
       }
     ]
   }
   ```

   Every bullet in the changelog section MUST have a corresponding entry in `bullets[]`. Do **not** include bullets for PRs you excluded.

7. **Run provenance validation** before writing `CHANGELOG.md`. Call:

   ```
   go run ./scripts/changelog-generation validate-provenance \
     --evidence /tmp/gh-aw/agent/evidence.json \
     --provenance /tmp/gh-aw/agent/provenance.json
   ```

   This validates that every bullet in `provenance.json` references a PR present in the evidence manifest and that PR numbers are not fabricated. It exits 0 on success and non-zero on failure, outputting a JSON result.

   - If validation **fails**: emit `noop` with the validation failure reason. Do **not** write `CHANGELOG.md` or push.
   - If validation **passes**: proceed to write `CHANGELOG.md`.

8. **Write `CHANGELOG.md`** using the rewriter. First write the new section body (without the header line) to `/tmp/gh-aw/agent/section.md`, then call:

   ```
   go run ./scripts/changelog-generation rewrite-changelog-section \
     --mode <unreleased|release> \
     [--target-version <version>] \
     --section-file /tmp/gh-aw/agent/section.md
   ```

   This handles both `unreleased` and `release` modes, preserves all other sections and the link footer exactly, and outputs a JSON result confirming success.

9. **Commit and push**:

   Commit only `CHANGELOG.md`.

   For **`release`** mode:
   - Commit message: `chore(changelog): update changelog for v${{ needs.pre_activation.outputs.target_version }}`
   - Use the `push-to-pull-request-branch` safe output to push to the triggering `prep-release-*` branch. Do **not** create a new PR — the release PR already exists.

   For **`unreleased`** mode (singleton branch/PR orchestration):
   - Commit message: `chore(changelog): update unreleased changelog section`
   - Use `create-pull-request` targeting branch `generated-changelog`. The framework handles branch creation and PR reuse — calling `create-pull-request` with the same branch name will force-push to the existing branch if it exists and reuse the open PR. Always call `create-pull-request` once regardless of whether the branch or PR already exists:
     - PR title: `chore: update CHANGELOG.md [Unreleased] section`
     - PR body (include all three elements):
       1. Date of generation (today's date in YYYY-MM-DD format)
       2. The compare range used: `${{ needs.pre_activation.outputs.compare_range }}`
       3. A note that this PR is auto-generated by the changelog-generation workflow and re-runs will overwrite the branch — do not make manual edits to the branch.
   - After `create-pull-request`, use `update-pull-request` to refresh the PR description with the new date and compare range.

10. **If no action is taken** (no user-facing PRs, or CHANGELOG.md is already up-to-date): emit `noop` with a clear reason. Do **not** push an empty commit.

## Constraints

- Generate changelog entries strictly at the **pull-request level**, not the commit level.
- Every bullet MUST end with `([#NNN](url))` citation linking to the real PR — no bullets without a PR citation.
- Write `/tmp/gh-aw/agent/provenance.json` with machine-readable bullet-to-PR mappings for every included bullet before writing CHANGELOG.md.
- Provenance validation (step 7) MUST pass before CHANGELOG.md is written or any push occurs.
- Do **not** modify any release sections other than the target section for this run.
- Do **not** change the file's link footer (e.g., `[Unreleased]: https://...` comparison links) — preserve them exactly.
- Do **not** invent categories or sub-headings not present in the existing file.
